    • Constructor Detail

      • SavedFile

        public SavedFile()
        Create a virtual non-existent file.

        Use this if you don't need a real file on the system but the configuration needs a File instance.

      • SavedFile

        public SavedFile(File folder,
                 String fileName,
                 String extension)
        Create a `SavedFile` instance from a parent abstract pathname and a child pathname string.
        Parameters:
        folder - The directory containing the configuration file.
        fileName - The name of the configuration file (without extension).
        extension - The extension (including the dot '.') of the configuration file.

      • SavedFile

        public SavedFile(File file)
        Create a `SavedFile` instance from a Java abstract pathname representation.
        Parameters:
        file - The abstract pathname of the configuration file.

    • Method Detail

      • init

        public boolean init()
        Initiate this configuration file.

        Creates parent folders and the file if not exists and not virtual.

        When `true` is returned, this SavedFile can be used safely.

        Returns:
        Returns `true` if the initialization was successful, `false` otherwise.
        See Also:
        isInitialized()

      • isInitialized

        public boolean isInitialized()
        Gets whenever this `SavedFile` has been initialized.
        Returns:
        Returns `true` if init() was called before.

      • canAccess

        public boolean canAccess()
        Returns true if it is currently possible to access and modify this file.
        Returns:
        true if this file is accessible
        See Also:
        lock()

      • lock

        public void lock()
        Locks this file to disable getting it.

        Warning: this operation is not reversible, use it carefully.

        getFile() will always return `null` after this operation.

      • getFile

        public File getFile()
